Should any members who see an application have a good reason for objecting, then they are asked to let a Recruitment Officer know their objections by sending a tell in game – not by posting on the thread. In the case of objections, the recruitment officer will discuss the matter with other officers in game before making a decision. If a decision is difficult, the matter will be referred to the guild leader for a final decision.<br><br>Recruitment Officers will regularly check the New members Forum, and where an applicant has received 3 supporting posts will make a final posting on the thread authorising membership.<br><br>When membership has been authorised, the applicant is asked to contact any officer in game to be invited formally to the guild.<br><br>When an applicant has been invited, the officer who had made the invitation is asked to record this fact on the thread in the New Members Forum, so that others are aware the invitation has been made.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm22.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm22.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm22.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm22.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign=